org.linqs.psl.util

Class Parallel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.linqs.psl.util.Parallel

  • public final class Parallel
extends Object
    Utilities to run operations in parallel. The threads will be started up on the first call, and not shut down until the JVM shuts down. Since the thread pool (and CPU) is shared, only one task may be run in parallel at a time.

      • count

        public static Parallel.RunTimings count(long start,
                                        long end,
                                        long increment,
                                        Parallel.Worker<Long> baseWorker)
        Count and call a worker with each number in [start, end). Inclusive with start, exclusive with end. The caller is trusted to provide appropriate numbers. The long value provided to the worker will be the number also passed as a Long.

      • foreachBatch

        public static <T> Parallel.RunTimings foreachBatch(Iterator<T> work,
                                                   int batchSize,
                                                   Parallel.Worker<List<T>> baseWorker)
        Invoke a worker once for each batch of items. This is like foreach() but instead of passing a single item, the parent thread will collect several items and pass those items together to the worker. This works well when there are many small computations that need to be done. The long value passed to the worker will be the number of items in the batch.
